item.title: Immigration's place in the Biden-Trump debate
item.description: Thursday night's debate between President Biden and former President Donald Trump comes on the heels of new data released by the White House that shows border crossings are down more than 40% in the three weeks since the president's immigration executive order. CBS News national security contributor Samantha Vinograd has more on how both candidates might approach the topic of immigration in the debate.
